  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db6\u0db1\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 1600\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A subsidy of 1600 crore rupees to buy organic fertilizers",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In the 2022/23 season of rice cultivation, 70 percent chemical fertilizers and 30 percent organic fertilizers have been recommended to the Ministry of Agriculture by the Department of Agriculture and scholars related to the agriculture sector. It is proposed to use a mixture of chemical fertilizers and organic fertilizers for paddy cultivation in the upcoming season.",
        "According to the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera said that in the next season, a bundle of 50 kg of urea fertilizer will be given to farmers at a price of 10,000 rupees, and 125 kg of urea fertilizer will be given per hectare.",
        "The minister also mentioned that the government has focused on providing a subsidy of 20,000 rupees to the farmers for buying organic fertilizers, while 30 percent of the environment-friendly fertilizers will be used in paddy cultivation. The amount expected to be spent by the government to provide this subsidy is 1600 crore rupees.",
        "Yesterday (17) afternoon, the minister called all the industrialists who are currently producing eco-friendly fertilizers in Sri Lanka to the Ministry of Agriculture to discuss the problems they are facing and whether they can complete the organic fertilizer requirement of 30 percent in the coming season. They were asked about the matter.",
        "The minister said that he also believes that some of the fertilizers that have been given to farmers claiming to be organic fertilizers in the last season are very inferior in quality and condition. The government has decided to provide even this subsidy to protect those industrialists.",
        "Therefore, if organic fertilizers are given to the farmers in this season, they will not be approved for their use without certification regarding their quality and standard, he said. He also mentioned that the Department of Agriculture has set up a work order to check the quality of some farmers if they produce the organic fertilizers they need.",
        "Currently, a bundle of urea fertilizer is sold for as high as 42000 rupees in the market. But the government provides a bundle of urea fertilizer for 10,000 rupees. Therefore, no other subsidy is given to the farmers who use urea fertilizers and the government has decided to give a subsidy of 20,000 rupees to the farmers for buying organic fertilizers.",
        "The minister also mentioned that the government will spend 1600 crore rupees for this subsidy."
      ],
